<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1591,1796]" box="[199,1331,1663,1687]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[370,443,1663,1687]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Northeast, Central-West and Southeast regions (CE, GO, MG) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro" box="[1165,1319,1663,1687]" firstAuthor="Ribeiro" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref42583" refString="Ribeiro, J. R. I. (2007) A review of the species of Belostoma Latreille, 1807 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Belostomatidae) from the four southeastern Brazilian states. Zootaxa, 1477, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="2007">Ribeiro 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,1591,1796]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Comments: Because 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1930" box="[434,541,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dallasi">
<emphasis box="[434,541,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. dallasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been misidentified as other species (namely 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1084,1201,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anurum">
<emphasis box="[1084,1201,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. anurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Peletier &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1825" box="[1214,1312,1700,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boscii">
<emphasis box="[1214,1312,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. boscii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1930" box="[151,259,1736,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dallasi">
<emphasis box="[151,259,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. dallasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could not be reliably applied to several specimens identified by De Carlo. For Brazilian specimens, the correct interpretation of this name has shown that the species seems to be confined to the three states above.
</paragraph>
